    <stitle>INSTRUMENTS - CLUSTER FAILURE DIAGNOSIS - VOLTMETER DISPLAY FAILURE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x0803404" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>VOLTMETER DISPLAY FAILURE</title>
        <figure id="f0803430" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0803430" filename="../figg08/G0803430.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Voltmeter Display</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>If the
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0803430">voltmeter display</hotlnk>
            is indicating a problem, the circuits that serve it must be checked for clean, tight, unbroken and
            non-shorted connections. If the circuits check OK, measure the appropriate voltage at the appropriate
            cluster harness connector (refer to
            <hotlnk document="s08034x_22.xml" xrefid="x0803403">CLUSTER HARNESS CONNECTORS</hotlnk>
            and GROUP 08, CIRCUIT DIAGRAMS). Turn the key switch to ACC and read across the accessory voltage and ground
            with a good test voltmeter. Replace the voltmeter display gauge if it does not read near the test accessory
            voltage.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
